ENTRY       EC 3.5.1.109                Enzyme
NAME        sphingomyelin deacylase;
            SM deacylase;
            GcSM deacylase;
            glucosylceramide sphingomyelin deacylase;
            sphingomyelin glucosylceramide deacylase;
            SM glucosylceramide GCer deacylase;
            SM-GCer deacylase;
            SMGCer deacylase
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on carbon-nitrogen bonds, other than peptide bonds;
            In linear amides
SYSNAME     N-acyl-sphingosylphosphorylcholine amidohydrolase
REACTION    (1) an N-acyl-sphingosylphosphorylcholine + H2O = a fatty acid + sphingosylphosphorylcholine;
            (2) a D-glucosyl-N-acylsphingosine + H2O = a fatty acid + D-glucosyl-sphingosine
SUBSTRATE   N-acyl-sphingosylphosphorylcholine;
            H2O [CPD:C00001];
            D-glucosyl-N-acylsphingosine [CPD:C01190]
PRODUCT     fatty acid [CPD:C00162];
            sphingosylphosphorylcholine;
            D-glucosyl-sphingosine
COMMENT     The enzyme is involved in the sphingolipid metabolism in the epidermis.
HISTORY     EC 3.5.1.109 created 2011
